metal. The rocket diameter can range from 3 meters to 10 meters according to your choice. Steel cheaper then titanium but titanium is stonger lower weigh  and more expensive.<br>
2. You can use either of these propellant combinations.<br>
1. Kerosine (RP1) + Liquid oxygen. (lok + lox)<br>
2. Liquid hydrogen + liquid Oxygen.( Lox + Loh)<br>
<br>
3. The Cyrogenic propellant or cyrogenic oxidizer tank must be insulated with kevlar to keep it super cold.<br>
<br>
4.  For Lox + lok use two 5/1 mass ratio stages to ensure<br>
there is enough fuel, and delta v to reach orbit.<br>
5. For lox + loh use two 3/1 mass ratio stages with<br>
Si = 450 seconds or use a little more mass ratio if<br>
Si is 400 seconds to ensure enough delta v and  <br>
fuel to reach orbit.<br>
6. Your rocket needs to be capable of achieving 10,000<br>
meters/sec at terminal stage burn out to ensure orbital<br>
injection.<br>
7. Use off the shelve rocket motors:  or build and test your own motors. Its your choice to make on that.<br>
8.You should plan on a short flight say two or 3 orbits maximium, if your riding in a space capsule to orbit.<br>
9. Three orbits requires about 270 minutes flight time,<br>
in a capsule. Thats 4.5 hours . Six orbits requires<br>
about 9 hours. This is going to be be a small claustrophobic capsule most likely:  so do not expect<br>
to be real comfortable physicaly. <br>
10. Use 4 triangular fins to make stage 1 fly straight<br>
through the atmosphere.Inertial guidance is much better<br>
but far more expensive.<br>
11. You can use a conical or a barrel shaped capsule with<br>
rounded top. Its your choice. Dimensions could be 3 meters wide by two meters high   or up to 10 meters<br>
wide  by 3 meters, high.On the top end of it you can put<br>
a few small port holes made of thick. and super strong  plexi glass, if you want.Enjoy the view of the earth<br>
12. Place an ablative heat shield made of pure silicon<br>
baked at 3000 C for several hours on the capsule. It needs to be  thick.<br>
13. On top of capsule place Steel or titanium hook,<br>
and 3 large parachutes  on it. <br>
14. Inside you will need a  steel acceleration rack with<br>
room for two or three persons in Gemini style  pressure suits on it.You need a good cooling, and heating system<br>
controled by thermostat in capsule. Walls of capsule should have three layers minimium construction  with kevar insulation between each layer of wall.<br>
15. The Rack needs strong leather straps to secure passengers snugly during launch.<br>
16. Under rack place lithium hydroxide canisters to clean air, air tanks, water tank, fuel cell power sources,<br>
and other rations and equipment. Make sure its all snug and secure there.<br>
17. Give each stage enough engine thrust to boost you at least 3 gs of accleration a second.<br>
18. If your rocket weighs 300,000 kilograms on the pad<br>
you want 900,000 KGf minimium thrust  on stage one engines. Thats about 2,000,000 pounds of thrust.<br>
19. If stage one has 5/1 mass ratio then its going to have 240,000 kg of fuel in it : then weight of its  tanks engines, and interstage shell can not exceed 48,000 kg.<br>
20. Then stage 2 with a 5/1 mass ratio will have 9400 kg of fuel in it. If you use the 5/1 mass fraction  then capsule, the stage 2 engine, and fuel  tanks weight can not exceed 2600 kg which is about 5800 pounds. You want a minimium thrust of 36,000 KGf from stage 2.<br>
Thats about 80,000 pounds of thrust.<br>
<br>
21. You may want to scale this up to a larger size such<br>
500,000 Kgf on the pad. If you do this , and <br>
do enough unmanned flight testing  to garuntee a reasonable probability of safe operation, then you can go<br>
into space. Also note the following If you use two 5/1 stages fueled by lok and lox your going to make an orbital<br>
manned space flight.If you use two 5/1 mass ratio stages<br>
fueled by Lox and Loh your going to have to shut down <br>
the stage two engine when you hit about 11,200 m/sec in delta v , then fly by the moon on a free return trajectory to earth. Then you must reenter the atmosphere at about 25,000 miles per hour . Make sure your heat shield can handle  reentry at that velocity or you burn up like a meteor, and you die during reentry .  and * IF YOU BURN ALL THE FUEL in stage 2  using lox + loh : using the 5/1 mass ratios , then stage 2  will accelerate you to from 12,800, too 14,400 m/sec<br>
in velocity. But if that happens then  you have a 1 way ticket to fly by  uranus and beyond , and returning to earth will be impossible for you because you do not have the fuel to declerate back into the inner solar system. If that  happens you die when your life support runs out and you orbit the sun forever in a a distant solar orbit as a frozen and lifeless corpse.<br>
Make sure you have the right stuff  before you try this.<br>
* If you mess up and make mistakes you die, and that<br>
is what will happen if you do not have the right stuff.<br>
Manned Space flight is a very danergous business to be in. So for private persons, and groups who want to do<br>
private manned space flight and who can afford it Here is your oppurtunity. Build It!  Fly it! Make it home alive <br>
? hopefully. If you use Lok + lox you can call your mission  Gemini 13 if you want too . If you use Lox + loh you can call your mission Apollo 18 if you want to.<br>
